HEADWORD: Weltschmertz
<hw>Welt"schmertz`</hw> <pr>(v⟦ecr⟧lt"shm⟦ecr⟧rts`)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[G., fr. <ets>welt</ets> world + <ets>schmertz</ets>
pain. See <er>World</er>; <er>Smart</er>, <pos>v. i.</pos>]</ety>
<def>Sorrow or sadness over the present or future evils or woes of the
world in general; sentimental pessimism.</def>⟦br⟧
